{
  "text": "Linkage disequilibrium (LD) is the square of the correlation coefficient (r 2 ) between markers. To investigate the extent of LD across the wheat genome and the markers that have a position on the consensus map [CITATION_1] , r 2 between intra chromosomal SNP markers was estimated using SAS 9.3. We plotted the intrachromosomal r 2 values against the genetic distance, using a nonlinear regression in SAS [CITATION_2] . The distance at which the LD decays to 0.7 was considered as the critical distance up to which a QTL region extends.",
